<HL>
   Mesaba Aviation's Traffic Rises
</HL>
<DATE>
08/09/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   ATCC
</CO>
<IN>
AIRLINES (AIR)
</IN>
<LP>
   MINNEAPOLIS -- AirTran Corp. said July traffic at its
Mesaba Aviation unit rose 24% to 20.6 million revenue
passenger miles from 16.6 million a year earlier. A revenue
passenger mile is one paying passenger flown one mile.
   The carrier's July load factor, or the percentage of
available seats occupied, dropped to 57.8% from 60.5%.
</LP>
