<TEXT>
   One of the little curses
   Of writing newspaper verses
   Is that these very pages
   Could line tomorrow's bird cages.
   However, there is a chance,
   In just the right circumstance,
   That they may be read once more
   On a refrigerator door.
   -- Pat D'Amico.
