<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   SHRP
</CO>
<LP>
   Sharper Image Corp., responding to dull sales and
earnings, said it would reduce its work force by 10% as part
of broader cost-cutting to improve its financial performance.
   The San Francisco-based specialty retailer has about 1,100
employees. Besides the layoffs, the company said "every area
of the business is under review" for possible
expense-cutting. It said it had already trimmed travel,
entertainment and supply budgets and had imposed a hiring
freeze.
